AB  - With the increasing adoption of new energy vehicle ,traditional fixed charging stations are increasingly inadequate in meeting dynamic charging demands. Distributed mobile wireless charging vehicles offer a novel approach to address bottlenecks in coverage and efficiency. This paper establishes a Markov Decision Process (MDP) model for charging vehicle scheduling based on deep reinforcement learning (DRL), employing the Deep Deterministic Policy Gradient (DDPG) algorithm to optimize charging vehicle path planning and task scheduling.Simulation results verify that the optimized scheme increases the charging fulfillment rate,reduces energy consumption, and decreases users' waiting time. This study provides both theoretical and practical support for intelligent scheduling in wireless charging systems. © 2025 IEEE.
