AB  - Automated guided vehicles (AGVs) are crucial transportation equipment that connects quay cranes (QCs) with yard cranes (YCs) in automated container terminals (ACTs). Ensuring real-time path planning without conflicts is vital for improving the operational efficiency and safety of ACTs. This paper studies the conflict-free AGV routing problem in ACTs with uncertainties. To improve the efficiency and safety of the ACT operations, we propose a deep reinforcement learning (DRL) method based on invalid action masking and artificial potential fields. In this method, we mask out invalid actions to resolve conflicts between AGVs. The reward-shaping strategy is based on the artificial potential field to handle the slow iteration of DRL algorithms due to sparse rewards. Simulation experiments verify the effectiveness of the proposed method.  © 2024 IEEE.
