UR  - https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/85215250947?origin=resultslist
AB  - Material delivery and product processing are two important components of intelligent manufacturing. Existing research mostly focuses on either job shop scheduling or vehicle scheduling. However, integrating vehicle scheduling in material delivery with job shop scheduling can effectively improve the production efficiency of enterprises. This paper investigates the flexible flow shop scheduling problem (FFSP) considering material delivery and process scheduling (FFSPDP). First, a mixed integer programming model is developed to minimize the sum of maximum completion times at each stage. Second, a hyper-heuristic algorithm based on deep reinforcement learning is proposed. Twelve low-level heuristic (LLH) operators are designed to perturb and optimize solutions, and a deep neural network is used to learn the relationship between the states of the solution and the LLH. This paper designs a new state space and reward function to improve the stability of deep neural network training. Then, two improved NEH2 algorithms are designed to initialize the population, which are used to improve the quality of the initial solution and improve the convergence speed of the algorithm. Finally, extensive comparative experiments validate the effectiveness and performance of the proposed method. The results show that the developed mathematical model and the algorithm proposed can effectively solve the investigated problem in this paper. © 2025
